                <h1>Dog Care Tips</h1>
                <p>Proper dog care is crucial to ensure that your pet lives a healthy and happy life. Below are some
                    essential tips for caring for your dog:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Regular Vet Visits:</strong> Ensure your dog visits the veterinarian annually for a
                        check-up and vaccinations.</li>
                    <li><strong>Proper Nutrition:</strong> Feed your dog a balanced diet suited to their age, health
                        status, and activity level.</li>
                    <li><strong>Exercise:</strong> Regular exercise helps keep your dog healthy. Aim for at least 30
                        minutes to 2 hours of activity each day depending on the breed.</li>
                    <li><strong>Grooming:</strong> Regular grooming, including brushing and bathing, is essential,
                        especially for breeds with long hair.</li>
                    <li><strong>Mental Stimulation:</strong> Keep your dog's mind active with toys, training, and plenty
                        of play.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>For more detailed guidance on dog care, visit <a href="https://www.akc.org/dog-care/">American Kennel
                        Club's Dog Care</a>, or visit <a
                        href="https://www.caninestyles.com/blogs/news/the-essential-guide-to-dog-care-10-tips-for-happy-and-healthy-dogs">The
                        Essential Guide to Dog Care by CanineStyles</a></p>
            </main>
